CSS Cheat Sheet

Reference:
*https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp
*https://css-tricks.com/almanac/

Cascading Style Sheets at the most basic level it indicates that the order of CSS rules matter. 


.class
#id
*---this is used to specify all items in the css, usualy used in the first section (
*{
Tetxt -align: left;
}


element
element, element ;;;; two elements with the same css 
element element   ;;;;; If we see something like this =>  h2 p {  } this means all p's inside h2's
element > element;;;; ; If we see something like this =>  h2 > p { } all p that have a parent of size 1  of h2 
element + element;;;;;; If we see something like this h2 + p { }  => select any p exactly after and not within  a h2 element 
H2+p :hover{} cahnge the mouse icon while hovering around the button 

:last-child
:first-child
!important (not recommended overrides any previreous or upcoming tags )


What seletors win out in the cascade depends on:
-Specificity
-Importance
-Source Order


